-- TAKE A LOOK-Pimco's Gross leaves firm he co-founded for Janus
-- 
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 05:52PM EDT
-- None



Sept 26 (Reuters) - Bill Gross, the money manager who became known as the Bond King for his prowess in running Pimco's flagship bond fund, took the industry by surprise on Friday by quitting Pimco for distant rival Janus Capital Group <JNS.N.>. The move followed record outflows from Pimco's flagship portfolio and clashes by Gross with other top executives.

